article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 49, Florida A&amp,M 46
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Kevan Creppy hit two free throws with 5.1 seconds to play, and C.J. Reed hit another with 3.9 seconds left, carrying Bethune-Cookman to a 49-46 victory over Florida A&M on Thursday night. Creppy and Reed led the Wildcats (16-15, 9-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) with 10 points each, while John Holmes grabbed a season-high 15 rebounds. Larry Jackson had 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Rattlers (9-20, 6-10), and Brandon Bryant added 11 points. The Rattlers led by six, 27-21, with 16:57 to play when Bethune-Cookman went on a 15-5 run to go up 36-32 with 10:33 remaining. The Wildcats used a couple of Alexander Starling baskets, plus free throws by Alvin Pegues and Reed to take a 46-44 edge with 55.2 seconds remaining. Then came the clinching free throws by Creppy and Reed, giving Bethune-Cookman four wins in its last five games.
